# dorv — agent collaboration

Full protocol: [docs/AGENT_COLLABORATION.md](../../docs/AGENT_COLLABORATION.md). Claims file: [.agents/claims.yaml](../../.agents/claims.yaml).

## Before coding

1. Resolve blockers: Linear `blockedBy` → description `## Depends on` → [LINEAR_DEPENDENCIES.md](../../docs/LINEAR_DEPENDENCIES.md) / [PRIORITIES.md](../../docs/PRIORITIES.md).
2. Read `.agents/claims.yaml` — if any blocker has `status: in_progress`, **wait** (tell user) or spawn background poll (≤ **6 h**, default **5 min** interval).
3. Scan blocker issues in Linear for `🤖 Agent claim` with `in_progress`.
4. Blocked + auto-continue: add `wait_queue` entry, post `🤖 Agent wait` on Linear, use **Task** tool to poll until `poll_until` or all blockers `done`, then claim → worktree → PR.

## Worktree (required)

- Create `.worktrees/feature-hum-####` with branch `feature/hum-####` before coding.
- All commits for that issue happen only in the worktree — not on `main` in the primary checkout.
- See [docs/AGENT_COLLABORATION.md](../../docs/AGENT_COLLABORATION.md#git-worktree-required).

## On claim (required)

1. Post Linear comment (`🤖 Agent claim`, `in_progress`, include **Worktree** path).
2. Update `.agents/claims.yaml` (`branch`, `worktree`, `depends_on`).
3. `git worktree add` then `cd` into the worktree.

## On finish (required)

1. Tests/lint pass in the worktree.
2. Push branch and **open PR** to `main` (`gh pr create`; title `HUM-####: …`).
3. Linear comment `done` with **PR** URL; yaml `pr:` + `status: done`.

Never implement while blockers are `in_progress` (background agent polls only until clear). Never mark `done` without a PR unless the user opts out. Max background wait: **6 hours** — then `expired` and notify user.
